很多[[神話|神話]]傳說和[[宗教|宗教]]敘事，涉及到同性之間的親密情感與情欲，或談到「性別變換」的神聖性。這些神話敘事可詮釋為一種表達[[LGBT|LGBT]]情感的形式，蘊藏著現代的性傾向和性別概念<ref name=lgbt_M>{{cite book|author1=Randy P. Conner|author2=Mariya Sparks|author3=David Hatfield Sparks|title=Cassell's Encyclopedia of Queer Myth, Symbol, and Spirit: Gay, Lesbian, Bisexual, and Transgender Lore|date=1997|publisher=Cassell|isbn=9780304337606|url=https://books.google.com.tw/books/about/Cassell_s_Encyclopedia_of_Queer_Myth_Sym.html?id=yGoYAAAAIAAJ&redir_esc=y|access-date=2015-11-14|archive-date=2018-01-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180123190510/https://books.google.com.tw/books/about/Cassell_s_Encyclopedia_of_Queer_Myth_Sym.html?id=yGoYAAAAIAAJ&redir_esc=y|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

[[美索不达米亚|美索不达米亚]][[吉爾伽美什史詩|吉爾伽美什史詩]]記載女神[[宁松|宁松]]之子[[吉爾伽美什|吉爾伽美什]]和其親密夥伴[[恩奇杜|恩奇杜]]結為至交好友的故事，[[塔納赫|塔納赫]][[撒母耳記|撒母耳記]]描述了[[大衛王|大衛王]]和[[約拿單|約拿單]]的深刻情誼，有些當代學者將他們詮釋為愛和情欲的關係<ref>{{cite book|author1=Susan Ackerman|title=When Heroes Love: The Ambiguity of Eros in the Stories of Gilgamesh and David|date=2005|publisher=Columbia University Press|isbn=9780231507257|pages=165–231|url=http://www.amazon.com/dp/0231132603}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author1=Jean-Fabrice Nardelli|title=Homosexuality and Liminality in the Gilgamesh and Samuel|date=2007|publisher=Hakkert|isbn=9789025606381|pages=28–63|url=https://books.google.com.tw/books/about/Homosexuality_and_liminality_in_the_Gilg.html?id=k8wXAQAAIAAJ&redir_esc=y|access-date=2015-11-14|archive-date=2015-11-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117023301/https://books.google.com.tw/books/about/Homosexuality_and_liminality_in_the_Gilg.html?id=k8wXAQAAIAAJ&redir_esc=y|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author1=Bruce L. Gerig|title=Jonathan & David: The Debate Continues|url=http://epistle.us/hbarticles/jondave11.html|accessdate=2015-11-14|archive-date=2015-11-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117030533/http://epistle.us/hbarticles/jondave11.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在[[古希臘神話|古希臘神話]]，不少男性神祇或[[英雄|英雄]]都有一位或多位男性愛人，例如[[宙斯|宙斯]]（和[[伽倪墨得斯|伽倪墨得斯]]）、[[阿波羅|阿波羅]]（和[[雅辛托斯|雅辛托斯]]）、[[戴奧尼索斯|戴奧尼索斯]]（和{{tsl|en|Ampelos|安普羅斯}}）、[[海克力斯|海克力斯]]（和[[伊奧勞斯|伊奧勞斯]]、[[海拉斯|海拉斯]]）、[[阿基里斯|阿基里斯]]（和[[帕特羅克洛斯|帕特羅克洛斯]]）等等，反映了古希臘時代的[[古希臘少年愛|少年愛]]傳統<ref>{{cite encyclopedia|title=Classical Mythology|encyclopedia=glbtq.com|url=http://www.glbtq.com/literature/classical_myth.html|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140415180456/http://www.glbtq.com/literature/classical_myth.html|archivedate=2014-04-15|access-date=2015-11-05}}</ref>。

[[阿芙蘿黛蒂|阿芙蘿黛蒂]]（[[維納斯|維納斯]]）及其屬神[[厄洛特斯|厄洛特斯]]（[[邱比特|邱比特]]）是守護男同性之愛的古希臘神明<ref name=lgbt_M/>{{rp|64}}<ref name=lgbt_M/>{{rp|133}}。[[古羅馬|古羅馬]]皇帝[[哈德良|哈德良]]的男寵[[安提諾烏斯|安提諾烏斯]]，死後和[[戴奧尼索斯|戴奧尼索斯]]（[[巴克科斯|巴克斯]]）等神有所[[綜攝|綜攝]]，在希臘和拉丁地區被奉為一位神祇受到崇拜，有時則只把他當作一位英雄<ref>{{cite book |title=Beloved and God: The Story of Hadrian and Antinous |last=Lambert |first=Royston |year=1984 |publisher=George Weidenfeld & Nicolson |location= |isbn= |ref=harv}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Antinous as Dionysos|url=http://museum.classics.cam.ac.uk/collections/casts/antinous-dionysos|accessdate=2017-04-03|archive-date=2017-04-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170404131541/http://museum.classics.cam.ac.uk/collections/casts/antinous-dionysos|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

